{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LC6tSRx7qtB6ajorAMaMEX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the probe logic is:\n- probe **passes** → state already present, apply is skipped\n- probe **fails** + `on_probe_fail=\"skip\"` → skip the unit (this is the default)\n\nWait, let me re-read:\n- \"probe passes → state already present, apply is skipped\"\n- \"probe fails + on_probe_fail='skip' (the default) → skip\"\n\nSo if the probe FAILS, and `on_probe_fail=skip`, it SKIPS the unit. But that means the apply never runs!\n\nThat can't be right for setup preconditions. \n\nLet me look at the documentation more carefully.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1620,"cache_read_input_tokens":33040,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1620},"output_tokens":36,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7593058f-1a2d-4f7b-98ff-9856eb415cbd","uuid":"96230c61-da95-45ed-b305-c9f38c5d509b","request_id":"req_011Cc48TgJtZidwsQjeRgguP"}
