{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019bCnYw5hb67hFuCgbTZfCh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The 3-node CockroachDB cluster is fully deployed and healthy. Here's what was created:\n\n**Resources deployed:**\n- `crdb-cluster` — headless ClusterIP:None service (26257 gRPC, 8080 HTTP) with `publishNotReadyAddresses: true`\n- `crdb-cluster-public` — public ClusterIP service (26257 gRPC, 8080 HTTP)\n- `crdb-cluster` StatefulSet — 3/3 pods Ready, `cockroachdb/cockroach:v24.1.0`, `Parallel` pod management\n- `crdb-cluster-pdb` — PodDisruptionBudget (`maxUnavailable: 1`) preserving quorum\n- 3 × 10Gi PVCs all Bound\n\n**Key decisions:**\n- `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` was required — the default `OrderedReady` blocks pod 1 and 2 until pod 0 is Ready, but CockroachDB can't become Ready until `cockroach init` is run with all nodes present (chicken-and-egg).\n- `publishNotReadyAddresses: true` on the headless service ensures DNS entries exist for joining nodes before they pass readiness checks.\n- `cockroach init` was run once all 3 pods reached Running state to bootstrap the cluster."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":669,"cache_read_input_tokens":45334,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":669},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7593058f-1a2d-4f7b-98ff-9856eb415cbd","uuid":"0073290f-b9ac-4cbd-854d-907b0bc58186","request_id":"req_011Cc48ontawPFJcp8sb1858"}
